answers.body_markdown:
Instead of using the 4-year-old JDBC driver [sqljdbc41.jar][1] directly, you should use a dependency management tool, for example, [Maven][2]. Then, as described in the [driver home page][3], it can be added to a Maven project by adding it as a dependency in the POM file with the following code:

    &lt;dependency&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.microsoft.sqlserver&lt;/groupId&gt;
        &lt;artifactId&gt;mssql-jdbc&lt;/artifactId&gt;
        &lt;version&gt;10.2.1.jre17&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;/dependency&gt;

See the [Maven Central Repository][4] for the latest version. 


  [1]: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=54670
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/index.html
  [3]: https://github.com/Microsoft/mssql-jdbc
  [4]: https://search.maven.org/artifact/com.microsoft.sqlserver/mssql-jdbc

